+- Locate (exact name): `tokensave_find_exact_symbol(name)`. One call. O(log n) index probe.
+- Locate (ranked, fuzzy): `tokensave_search(query, limit)`. Use when you don't know the exact name.
+- Read source of a function/class/struct/etc: `tokensave_body(symbol, limit=1)`. One call. Returns the full body text.
+- Whole-task context (loc + related code): `tokensave_context(task="<question>")`. Use this when the prompt is open-ended.
+- Edit a function/method/class body: `tokensave_replace_symbol(symbol, new_source)`. The new_source MUST include the symbol's own declaration line (e.g. `def foo(...):`). Reindex is automatic.
+- Insert near a symbol: `tokensave_insert_at_symbol(symbol, content, position="before"|"after")`. For non-symbol locations use `tokensave_insert_at(path, anchor, content)`.
+- Add a field to a Prisma model or TS interface/type: NO direct tokensave tool — use `Edit` or `tokensave_str_replace(path, old_str, new_str)`. Re-run after to verify the edit landed.
+- Move a symbol across files: NO direct tokensave tool — combine `tokensave_body` (read), `tokensave_str_replace` (delete from source file + paste in target file), and `Edit` for import-site fixups.
+- Detect cycles: `tokensave_circular`. Do not infer manually.
+- Detect duplicates: `tokensave_similar(name|file)`. Enumerate the pairs returned. The MCP tool surfaces semantic neighbors, not strict duplicates — interpret accordingly.
+- Diff between refs/branches: `tokensave_branch_diff(base, head)` for tracked branches, or `tokensave_changelog` for commit-based diffs.
+- Call chain between two symbols: resolve both with `tokensave_find_exact_symbol`, then `tokensave_call_chain(from_id, to_id)`.
+- Callers/callees of a symbol: `tokensave_callers(node_id)` / `tokensave_callees(node_id)` after resolving via `tokensave_find_exact_symbol`.
+- Files importing X: `tokensave_file_dependents(file)`.
+- Impact radius (transitive dependents): `tokensave_impact(node_id)`.
+- Dead code: `tokensave_dead_code`.
+- Orphan env vars / Dockerfile audits: tokensave does NOT analyse these — use `Read` on `.env*` and `Dockerfile`, then judgment. Cite IDs from `GROUND_TRUTH.json` (`SECRET-*`, `ORPHAN-*`, `UNDECL-*`, `DOCKER-*`, `INFRA-*`).
+- After empty `tokensave_find_exact_symbol`: fall back to `tokensave_search`. After empty `tokensave_search`: `Read`/`Grep` are allowed for non-indexed files (`.prisma`, `.sql`, `.graphql`, `.proto`, `.env*`, `Dockerfile`).
 
